090-5 |ref= {{Harvid|Branch|2009}} }}\n:{{Cite journal\n |last1= \u2014\u2014\u2014 |first1= <!--N/A--> |last2= Cheeseman |first2= Nicholas |year= 2006\n |title= The Politics of Control in Kenya: Understanding the Bureaucratic-Executive State, 1952\u201378\n |journal= [[Review of African Political Economy]] |volume= 33 |issue= 107 |pages= 11\u201331\n |jstor= 4007109 |ref= {{Harvid|Branch|Cheeseman|2006}} |doi=10.1080/03056240600671183}}\n:{{Cite book\n |last= Brantley |first= Cynthia |year= 1981\n |title= The Giriama and Colonial Resistance in Kenya, 1800\u20131920\n |location= Berkeley and Los Angeles,&nbsp;CA |publisher= University of California Press\n |isbn= 978-0-520-04216-2 |ref= harv }}\n:{{Cite book\n |last= Carothers |first= John Colin |year= 1953\n |title= The African Mind in Health and Disease: A Study in Ethnopsychiatry\n |location= Geneva |publisher= [[World Health Organization]]\n |ref= harv |hdl= 10665/41138 |isbn= 9789241400176 }}\n:{{Cite web\n |last1= Carter |first1= Morris|year= 1934\n |title= The Kenya Land Commission Report\n |url= https://www.scribd.com/doc/74835533/CAB-24-248-The-Kenya-Land-Commission-Report-1934\n |location= London |publisher= Government Printer\n |ref= harv |display-authors=etal}}\n:{{Cite journal |last= Chappell |first= Stephen |year= 2011 |title= Air Power in the Mau Mau Conflict: The Government's Chief Weapon |url= http://www.rusi.org/downloads/assets/RUSI_Journal_Feb_2011_Chappell.pdf |journal= [[RUSI Journal]] |volume= 156 |issue= 1 |pages= 64\u201370 |doi= 10.1080/03071847.2011.559986 |ref= harv |url-status= dead |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20131020080650/http://www.rusi.org/downloads/assets/RUSI_Journal_Feb_2011_Chappell.pdf |archivedate= 20 October 2013 |df= dmy-all }}\n:{{Cite book\n |last= Clough |first= Marshall S. |year= 1998\n |title= Mau Mau Memoirs: History, Memory and Politics\n |location= Boulder,&nbsp;CO |publisher= Lynne Rienner Publishers\n |isbn= 978-1-555-87537-4 |ref= harv }}\n:{{Cite jou