etails/decolonizationin0000unse/page/25 }}\n:{{Cite journal\n |last= Berman |first= Bruce |year= 1991\n |title= Nationalism, Ethnicity, and Modernity: The Paradox of Mau Mau\n |url= https://www.scribd.com/doc/94922305/BERMAN-Bruce-1991-Nationalism-Ethnicity-and-Modernity-The-Paradox-of-Mau-Mau\n |journal= [[Canadian Journal of African Studies]] |volume= 25 |issue= 2 |pages= 181\u2013206\n |jstor= 485216 |ref= harv }}\n:{{Cite book\n |last= \u2014\u2014\u2014 |first= <!--N/A--> |year= 1990\n |title= Control & Crisis in Colonial Kenya: The Dialectic of Domination\n |location= Oxford |publisher= James Currey\n |isbn= 978-0-852-55069-4 |ref= {{Harvid|Berman|1990}} }}\n:{{Cite journal\n |last= Blacker |first= John |year= 2007\n |title= The Demography of Mau Mau: Fertility and Mortality in Kenya in the 1950s: A Demographer's Viewpoint\n |journal= [[African Affairs]] |volume= 106 |issue= 423 |pages= 205\u2013227\n |jstor= 4496439 |ref= harv |doi=10.1093/afraf/adm014}}\n:{{Cite journal\n |last= Branch |first= Daniel |year= 2007\n |title= The Enemy Within: Loyalists and the War Against Mau Mau in Kenya\n |url= https://ore.exeter.ac.uk/repository/bitstream/handle/10036/30200/Branch%20Enemy%20Within.pdf\n |journal= [[The Journal of African History]] |volume= 48 |issue= 2 |pages= 291\u2013315\n |jstor= 4501043 |ref= harv |doi=10.1017/s0021853707002812|hdl= 10036/30200 }} {{open access}}\n:{{Cite book\n |last= \u2014\u2014\u2014 |first= <!--N/A--> |year= 2009\n |title= Defeating Mau Mau, Creating Kenya: Counterinsurgency, Civil War, and Decolonization\n |location= New York,&nbsp;NY |publisher= Cambridge University Press\n |isbn= 978-0-521-13090-5 |ref= {{Harvid|Branch|2009}} }}\n:{{Cite journal\n |last1= \u2014\u2014\u2014 |first1= <!--N/A--> |last2= Cheeseman |first2= Nicholas |year= 2006\n |title= The Politics of Control in Kenya: Understanding the Bureaucratic-Executive State, 1952\u201378\n |journal= [[Review of African Political Economy]] |volume= 33 |issue= 107 |pages= 11\