{"title_page": "Mukesh Bhakar", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name             = Mukesh Bhakar\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|6 May 1988|df=y}}\n| honorific-suffix = MLA Ladnun\n| image            = Mukesh Bhakar at Ladnun SDM Office for nomination.jpg\n| caption          = Bhakar at Ladnun SDM office\n| imagesize        = 250 px\n| birth_name       = Mukesh Bhakar\n| birth_place      = [[Ladnun, Rajasthan]], India\n| office1           = Member of Legislative Assembly (MLA) Ladnun\n| termstart1        = 17 December 2018\n| term_end1        = \n| assembly1        = [[Ladnun (Rajasthan Assembly constituency)|Ladnun]]\n| office2          = State President, [[Rajasthan Youth Congress]]\n| term_start2      = 7 April 2020\n| office3          = State President, [[National Students' Union of India]]\n| term_start3      = January 2013\n| term_end3        = May 2015\n| office4          = [[National Students Union of India|National Secretary]]\n| term_start4      = 21 October 2015\n| term_end4        = 26 May 2018\n| office5          = Vice President of the [[Rajasthan Youth Congress]]\n| term_start5      = 22 November 2017\n| term_end5        = 6 April 2020\n| party            = [[Indian National Congress]]\n| parents          = Retd. Subedar Surjaram Bhakar (father)<br />Sohini Devi (mother)\n| alma_mater       = [[University of Rajasthan]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|BA]])<br /> [[University of Rajasthan|University of Rajasthan]] ([[Master of Arts|MA]])\n}}\n\n'''Mukesh Bhakar''' (born 6 May 1988) is an Indian politician who is serving as the President of the [[Rajasthan Youth Congress]], he represents also in [[Rajasthan Legislative Assembly]] from [[Ladnu|Ladnun]] of [[Nagaur district]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rajassembly.nic.in/MemberBioData.aspx|title=Rajasthan Legislative Assembly Member Information|website=rajassembly.nic.in}}</ref> As member of the [[Indian National Congress|Congress party]] <ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.rajpcc.com/mukeshbhakar|title=Indian National Congress Party|website=www.rajpcc.com}}</ref>. Bhakar was previously State President of [[National Students' Union of India]] Rajasthan, the student wing of [[Indian National Congress]] from 2013 to 2015.\n\n== Political life ==\nHe elected State President of [[National Students' Union of India]] Rajasthan in 2013.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/news/RAJ-JAI-mukesh-bhakar-became-the-state-chief-of-nsui-4164425-NOR.html|title=NSUI \u0915\u0947 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0926\u0947\u0936\u093e\u0927\u094d\u092f\u0915\u094d\u0937 \u092c\u0928\u0947 \u092e\u0941\u0915\u0947\u0936 \u092d\u093e\u0915\u0930|date=31 January 2013|website=Dainik Bhaskar}}</ref>  During his tenure NSUI made come back in [[University of Rajasthan]] after 12 years in the Largest University of Rajasthan.<ref>https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/jaipur/news/RAJ-JAI-10-candidates-for-presidents-post-rajasthan-4719233-NOR.html.</ref> After completion of his term National president nominated him National Secretary. Congress Party gave him an opportunity to contest Rajasthan State assembly elections 2018, where he successfully managed a win by margin of 12947 votes against 3 times MLA [[Thakur Manohar Singh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/election-result-2018/rajasthan-election-result-2018/nagaur/ladnun/mukesh-bhakar/|title=Ladnun Congress Candidate Mukesh Bhakar, Mukesh Bhakar vs Manohar Singh, \u0932\u093e\u0921\u0928\u0942\u0902 \u0938\u0940\u091f \u0938\u0947 \u0915\u093e\u0902\u0917\u094d\u0930\u0947\u0938 \u0909\u092e\u094d\u092e\u0940\u0926\u0935\u093e\u0930 \u092e\u0941\u0915\u0947\u0936 \u092d\u0915\u0930|website=Dainik Bhaskar}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/elections/rajasthan-election/article/ladnun-assembly-constituency-election-2018-rajasthan-assembly-polls-rajasthan-vasundhara-raje-bharatiya-janata-party-bjp-congress-sachin-pilot-manohar/320646|title=Ladnun Assembly Election Results 2018: Congress' Mukesh Bhakar won by 12,947 votes against BJP's sitting MLA|website=www.timesnownews.com}}</ref>. He won election for State President, [[Rajasthan Youth Congress]] over nearest candidate [[Amardin]] by 9872 votes.<ref>https://www.jagran.com/rajasthan/jaipur-congress-mla-mukesh-bhakar-appointed-as-rajasthan-pradesh-youth-congress-state-president-organization-elections-20172785.html</ref>\n\n== Positions held ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Position\n|-\n| 2009 - 10 || Unit President, National Students Union of India, University of Rajasthan\n|-\n| 2013 - 15 ||State President, National Students Union of India, NSUI Rajasthan\n|-\n| 2015 - 18 || National Secretary, National Students Union of India\n|-\n| 2018 \u2013 20  || State Vice President, Rajasthan Youth Congress\n|-\n| 2017 \u2013 cont. || PCC Member, Rajasthan Pradesh Congress Committee\n|-\n| 2017 \u2013 cont. || Member, All India Congress Committee\n|-\n| 2018 \u2013 cont. ||Member of Legislative Assembly (MLA) from Ladnun, Rajasthan State Assembly\n|-\n| 2019 \u2013 cont.  || Member of Committee on Petitions, Rajasthan State Assembly\n|-\n| 2020 \u2013 cont.  || State President, Rajasthan Youth Congress\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{twitter.com|mukeshbhakar_}}\n\n{{Indian National Congress}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bhakar, Mukesh}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Rajasthani people]]\n[[Category:Indian National Congress politicians]]\n[[Category:Rajasthani politicians]]\n[[Category:Rajasthan MLAs 2018\u2013]]\n[[Category:People from Nagaur district]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Indian politician}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2019}}\n{{Infobox officeholder\n| name             = Mukesh Bhakar\n| birth_date       = {{birth date and age|6 May 1988|df=y}}\n| honorific-suffix = MLA Ladnun\n| image            = Mukesh Bhakar at Ladnun SDM Office for nomination.jpg\n| caption          = Bhakar at Ladnun SDM office\n| imagesize        = 250 px\n| birth_name       = Mukesh Bhakar\n| birth_place      = [[Ladnun, Rajasthan]], India\n| office1           = Member of Legislative Assembly (MLA) Ladnun\n| termstart1        = 17 December 2018\n| term_end1        = \n| assembly1        = [[Ladnun (Rajasthan Assembly constituency)|Ladnun]]\n| office2          = State President of the [[Rajasthan Youth Congress]]\n| term_start2      = 7 April 2020\n| office3          = State President, [[National Students' Union of India]]\n| term_start3      = January 2013\n| term_end3        = May 2015\n| office4          = [[National Students Union of India|National Secretary]]\n| term_start4      = 21 October 2015\n| term_end4        = 26 May 2018\n| office5          = Vice President of the [[Rajasthan Youth Congress]]\n| term_start5      = 22 November 2017\n| term_end5        = 6 April 2020\n| party            = [[Indian National Congress]]\n| parents          = Retd. Subedar Surjaram Bhakar (father)<br />Sohini Devi (mother)\n| alma_mater       = [[University of Rajasthan]] ([[Bachelor of Arts|BA]])<br /> [[University of Rajasthan|University of Rajasthan]] ([[Master of Arts|MA]])\n}}\n\n'''Mukesh Bhakar''' (born 6 May 1988) is an Indian politician who is serving as the President of the [[Rajasthan Youth Congress]], he represents also in [[Rajasthan Legislative Assembly]] from [[Ladnu|Ladnun]] of [[Nagaur district]] <ref>{{Cite web|url=https://rajassembly.nic.in/MemberBioData.aspx|title=Rajasthan Legislative Assembly Member Information|website=rajassembly.nic.in}}</ref> As member of the [[Indian National Congress|Congress party]] <ref name=\"auto\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.rajpcc.com/mukeshbhakar|title=Indian National Congress Party|website=www.rajpcc.com}}</ref>. Bhakar was previously State President of [[National Students' Union of India]] Rajasthan, the student wing of [[Indian National Congress]] from 2013 to 2015.\n\n== Political life ==\nHe elected State President of [[National Students' Union of India]] Rajasthan in 2013.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/news/RAJ-JAI-mukesh-bhakar-became-the-state-chief-of-nsui-4164425-NOR.html|title=NSUI \u0915\u0947 \u092a\u094d\u0930\u0926\u0947\u0936\u093e\u0927\u094d\u092f\u0915\u094d\u0937 \u092c\u0928\u0947 \u092e\u0941\u0915\u0947\u0936 \u092d\u093e\u0915\u0930|date=31 January 2013|website=Dainik Bhaskar}}</ref>  During his tenure NSUI made come back in [[University of Rajasthan]] after 12 years in the Largest University of Rajasthan.<ref>https://www.bhaskar.com/rajasthan/jaipur/news/RAJ-JAI-10-candidates-for-presidents-post-rajasthan-4719233-NOR.html.</ref> After completion of his term National president nominated him National Secretary. Congress Party gave him an opportunity to contest Rajasthan State assembly elections 2018, where he successfully managed a win by margin of 12947 votes against 3 times MLA [[Thakur Manohar Singh]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bhaskar.com/election-result-2018/rajasthan-election-result-2018/nagaur/ladnun/mukesh-bhakar/|title=Ladnun Congress Candidate Mukesh Bhakar, Mukesh Bhakar vs Manohar Singh, \u0932\u093e\u0921\u0928\u0942\u0902 \u0938\u0940\u091f \u0938\u0947 \u0915\u093e\u0902\u0917\u094d\u0930\u0947\u0938 \u0909\u092e\u094d\u092e\u0940\u0926\u0935\u093e\u0930 \u092e\u0941\u0915\u0947\u0936 \u092d\u0915\u0930|website=Dainik Bhaskar}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/elections/rajasthan-election/article/ladnun-assembly-constituency-election-2018-rajasthan-assembly-polls-rajasthan-vasundhara-raje-bharatiya-janata-party-bjp-congress-sachin-pilot-manohar/320646|title=Ladnun Assembly Election Results 2018: Congress' Mukesh Bhakar won by 12,947 votes against BJP's sitting MLA|website=www.timesnownews.com}}</ref>. He won election for State President, [[Rajasthan Youth Congress]] over nearest candidate [[Amardin]] by 9872 votes.<ref>https://www.jagran.com/rajasthan/jaipur-congress-mla-mukesh-bhakar-appointed-as-rajasthan-pradesh-youth-congress-state-president-organization-elections-20172785.html</ref>\n\n== Positions held ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Position\n|-\n| 2009 - 10 || Unit President, National Students Union of India, University of Rajasthan\n|-\n| 2013 - 15 ||State President, National Students Union of India, NSUI Rajasthan\n|-\n| 2015 - 18 || National Secretary, National Students Union of India\n|-\n| 2018 \u2013 20  || State Vice President, Rajasthan Youth Congress\n|-\n| 2017 \u2013 cont. || PCC Member, Rajasthan Pradesh Congress Committee\n|-\n| 2017 \u2013 cont. || Member, All India Congress Committee\n|-\n| 2018 \u2013 cont. ||Member of Legislative Assembly (MLA) from Ladnun, Rajasthan State Assembly\n|-\n| 2019 \u2013 cont.  || Member of Committee on Petitions, Rajasthan State Assembly\n|-\n| 2020 \u2013 cont.  || State President, Rajasthan Youth Congress\n|-\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{twitter.com|mukeshbhakar_}}\n\n{{Indian National Congress}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bhakar, Mukesh}}\n[[Category:1988 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Rajasthani people]]\n[[Category:Indian National Congress politicians]]\n[[Category:Rajasthani politicians]]\n[[Category:Rajasthan MLAs 2018\u2013]]\n[[Category:People from Nagaur district]]\n", "name_user": "Mukesh Bhakar 0013", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mukesh_Bhakar"}
{"title_page": "Belle and Sebastian (2017 TV series)", "text_new": "{{About|the 2017 animated television series||Belle and Sebastian (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Belle and Sebastian\n| image                    = Belle and Sebastian title card.png\n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = English title screen.\n| genre                    = [[Historical]]<br />[[Adventure fiction|Adventure]]<br />[[Comedy-drama]]\n| creator                  = \n| developer                = Jean-Phillipe Robin\n| based_on                 = {{based on|''[[Belle et S\u00e9bastien]]''|[[C\u00e9cile Aubry]]}}\n| writer                   = \n| director                 = Lionel Francois\n| creative_director        = \n| voices                   = {{Plainlist|\n* '''English:'''\n* [[Angela Galuppo]]\n* [[Terrence Scammell (Canadian actor)|Terrence Scammell]]\n* [[Arthur Holden]]\n* Brittany Drisdelle\n* [[Sonja Ball]]\n* [[Vlasta Vr\u00e1na]]\n* Jessica Kardos\n* '''French:'''\n* Pascale Montreuil\n* Tristan Harvey\n* Kim Jalabert\n* Ludivine Dub\u00e9-Reding\n* Hugolin Chevrette-Landesque\n* Benoit Bri\u00e9re}}\n| theme_music_composer     = Music and lyrics by [[B\u00e9atrice Martin]]; Direction and arrangement by Renaud Bastien\n| opentheme                = \"Belle and Sebastian\" performed by [[C\u0153ur de pirate]]\n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = HITnRUN\n| country                  = Canada <br /> France\n| language                 = English <br /> French\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_series               = \n| num_episodes             = 52\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = Fran\u00e7ois Trudel<br /> Vincent Leroux<br />Nicolas Atlan<br />Sidonie Dumas<br/>[[Christophe Riandee|Christophe Riand\u00e9e]]\n| producer                 = Marc Dhrami <br /> Fran\u00e7ois Trudel\n| editor                   = Patrick Phelpin<br />Anne-Claire de Heredia\n| location                 = \n| cinematography           = \n| camera                   = \n| runtime                  = 11 minutes\n| company                  = [[Gaumont Animation]]<br />Groupe PVP\n| distributor              = [[Gaumont Animation]]\n| network                  = [[Ici Radio-Canada T\u00e9l\u00e9]] / [[Knowledge Network]] {{Small|(Canada)}}<br />[[M6 (France)|M6]] / [[Piwi +]] {{Small|(France)}}\n| picture_format           = [[1080p]] ([[16:9]] [[HDTV]])\n| audio_format             = \n| first_run                = \n| released                 = \n| first_aired              = \n| last_aired               = \n| related                  = \n| website                  = \n| production_website       = https://www.pvp.ca/en/productions/belle-and-sebastian\n}}\n\n'''''Belle and Sebastian''''' ({{Lang-fr|link=no|Belle et S\u00e9bastien}}) is an animated children's television series, an adaptations of the 1965 [[Belle et S\u00e9bastien|novel of the same name]] by [[C\u00e9cile Aubry]]. A Canada-France [[international co-production]], the series was produced by the Montreal-based Groupe PVP and France's [[Gaumont Animation]].\n\n==Production==\n\nOn September 2, 2015, American entertainment trade publication ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' reported that [[Gaumont Animation]] were developing an animated series based on [[C\u00e9cile Aubry|C\u00e9cile Aubry's]] novel ''[[Belle et S\u00e9bastien]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/global/belle-and-sebastian-pierre-belaisch-calimero-biarritz-les-rendez-vous-1201584012/|title=Biarritz Rendez-Vous: Gaumont Animation to Develop 'Belle and Sebastian' (EXCLUSIVE)|first=Emilio|last=Mayorga|date=September 2, 2015|accessdate=June 2, 2018|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]}}</ref> Later that month, Montreal-based Groupe PVP formed a coproduction partnership with Gaumont on two animated series, including ''Belle'', which was estimated to begin production in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://playbackonline.ca/2015/09/28/groupe-pvp-gaumont-animation-pact-on-two-series/|title=Groupe PVP, Gaumont Animation pact on two series|work=[[Playback (magazine)|Playback]]|publisher=[[Brunico Communications]]|date=September 29, 2015|accessdate=June 2, 2018|first=Julianna|last=Cummins}}</ref>\n\nThe show was produced for a consortium of broadcasters, including [[Ici Radio-Canada T\u00e9l\u00e9]] and [[Knowledge Network]] in Canada, [[M6 (France)|M6]] and [[Piwi +]] in France, [[Zweites Deutsches Fernsehen|ZDF]] in Germany, [[Vlaamse Radio- en Televisieomroeporganisatie|VRT]] in Belgium, and [[Radio T\u00e9l\u00e9vision Suisse|RTS]] in Switerzland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/global/gaumont-zdf-team-on-belle-et-sebastien-1201698234/|title=Gaumont Television, ZDF Team on 'Belle et Sebastien'|first=Else|last=Keslassy|date=February 2, 2016|accessdate=June 2, 2018|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]}}</ref>\n\n==Broadcast==\nThe series first began airing on [[Ici Radio-Canada T\u00e9l\u00e9]] on September 9, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ici.radio-canada.ca/jeunesse/scolaire/blogues/211/5-super-nouvelles-emissions/blogue|title=5 super nouvelles \u00e9missions|date=September 4, 2017|work=[[Ici Radio-Canada T\u00e9l\u00e9]]|publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]]|accessdate=June 2, 2018}}</ref> It premiered in France on [[M6 (France)|M6]] on October 9, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.gaumont.fr/2017/09/belle-et-sebastien-debarquent-sur-vos-petits-ecrans/|title=Belle et S\u00e9bastien d\u00e9barquent sur vos petits \u00e9crans !|date=September 20, 2017|accessdate=June 2, 2018|work=Gaumont Le Blog|publisher=[[Gaumont Film Company]]}}</ref> In the United States, the series began airing on [[TiVi5MONDE]] on June 13, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/Tivi5MondeUSA/videos/1820840601309147/|title=\"Belle et S\u00e9bastien\" on TiVi5MONDE starting June 13|work=[[TiVi5MONDE]]|date=June 12, 2018|accessdate=December 18, 2018}}</ref> In Germany, the show premiered on [[KiKa]] on September 22, 2018.<ref>{{cite press-release|url=https://www.presseportal.de/pm/6535/4065638|title=Freundschaft zwischen Kind und Hund: \"Belle und Sebastian\" (ZDF) Premiere der 52-teiligen Animationsserie ab 22. September 2018 bei KiKA|date=September 19, 2018|accessdate=December 18, 2018|publisher=[[ARD (broadcaster)|ARD]]/[[ZDF]]|location=Erfurt|agency=Presse Portal}}</ref>\n\nThe show had its English language debut on [[Knowledge Network]] on October 7, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/knowledgekids/videos/961989060625640/|title=Knowledge Kids Posts|work=[[Knowledge Network]]|date=September 29, 2017|accessdate=June 2, 2018}}</ref> In Singapore, it began airing on [[Channel 5 (Singapore)|Channel 5's]] [[Okto]] block on June 7, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tv.toggle.sg/en/channel5/shows/belle-sebastian/info|title=Belle & Sebastian Show Info|work=[[Okto]]|publisher=[[Mediacorp]]|accessdate=June 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2010s Canadian animated television series]]\n[[Category:2010s French animated television series]]\n[[Category:2017 French television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2017 Canadian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated adventure television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated drama television series]]\n[[Category:French children's animated adventure television series]]\n[[Category:French children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:French children's animated drama television series]]\n[[Category:Gaumont Animation]]\n", "text_old": "{{About|the 2017 animated television series||Belle and Sebastian (disambiguation)}}\n{{Infobox television\n| show_name                = Belle and Sebastian\n| image                    = Belle and Sebastian title card.png\n| image_alt                = \n| caption                  = English title screen.\n| genre                    = [[Historical]]<br />[[Adventure fiction|Adventure]]<br />[[Comedy-drama]]\n| creator                  = \n| developer                = Jean-Phillipe Robin\n| based_on                 = {{based on|''[[Belle et S\u00e9bastien]]''|[[C\u00e9cile Aubry]]}}\n| writer                   = \n| director                 = Lionel Francois\n| creative_director        = \n| voices                   = {{Plainlist|\n* '''English:'''\n* [[Angela Galuppo]]\n* [[Terrence Scammell (Canadian actor)|Terrence Scammell]]\n* [[Arthur Holden]]\n* Brittany Drisdelle\n* [[Sonja Ball]]\n* [[Vlasta Vr\u00e1na]]\n* [[Jessica Kardos]]\n* '''French:'''\n* Pascale Montreuil\n* Tristan Harvey\n* Kim Jalabert\n* Ludivine Dub\u00e9-Reding\n* Hugolin Chevrette-Landesque\n* Benoit Bri\u00e9re}}\n| theme_music_composer     = Music and lyrics by [[B\u00e9atrice Martin]]; Direction and arrangement by Renaud Bastien\n| opentheme                = \"Belle and Sebastian\" performed by [[C\u0153ur de pirate]]\n| endtheme                 = \n| composer                 = HITnRUN\n| country                  = Canada <br /> France\n| language                 = English <br /> French\n| num_seasons              = 1\n| num_series               = \n| num_episodes             = 52\n| list_episodes            = \n| executive_producer       = Fran\u00e7ois Trudel<br /> Vincent Leroux<br />Nicolas Atlan<br />Sidonie Dumas<br/>[[Christophe Riandee|Christophe Riand\u00e9e]]\n| producer                 = Marc Dhrami <br /> Fran\u00e7ois Trudel\n| editor                   = Patrick Phelpin<br />Anne-Claire de Heredia\n| location                 = \n| cinematography           = \n| camera                   = \n| runtime                  = 11 minutes\n| company                  = [[Gaumont Animation]]<br />Groupe PVP\n| distributor              = [[Gaumont Animation]]\n| network                  = [[Ici Radio-Canada T\u00e9l\u00e9]] / [[Knowledge Network]] {{Small|(Canada)}}<br />[[M6 (France)|M6]] / [[Piwi +]] {{Small|(France)}}\n| picture_format           = [[1080p]] ([[16:9]] [[HDTV]])\n| audio_format             = \n| first_run                = \n| released                 = \n| first_aired              = \n| last_aired               = \n| related                  = \n| website                  = \n| production_website       = https://www.pvp.ca/en/productions/belle-and-sebastian\n}}\n\n'''''Belle and Sebastian''''' ({{Lang-fr|link=no|Belle et S\u00e9bastien}}) is an animated children's television series, an adaptations of the 1965 [[Belle et S\u00e9bastien|novel of the same name]] by [[C\u00e9cile Aubry]]. A Canada-France [[international co-production]], the series was produced by the Montreal-based Groupe PVP and France's [[Gaumont Animation]].\n\n==Production==\n\nOn September 2, 2015, American entertainment trade publication ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'' reported that [[Gaumont Animation]] were developing an animated series based on [[C\u00e9cile Aubry|C\u00e9cile Aubry's]] novel ''[[Belle et S\u00e9bastien]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/global/belle-and-sebastian-pierre-belaisch-calimero-biarritz-les-rendez-vous-1201584012/|title=Biarritz Rendez-Vous: Gaumont Animation to Develop 'Belle and Sebastian' (EXCLUSIVE)|first=Emilio|last=Mayorga|date=September 2, 2015|accessdate=June 2, 2018|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]}}</ref> Later that month, Montreal-based Groupe PVP formed a coproduction partnership with Gaumont on two animated series, including ''Belle'', which was estimated to begin production in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://playbackonline.ca/2015/09/28/groupe-pvp-gaumont-animation-pact-on-two-series/|title=Groupe PVP, Gaumont Animation pact on two series|work=[[Playback (magazine)|Playback]]|publisher=[[Brunico Communications]]|date=September 29, 2015|accessdate=June 2, 2018|first=Julianna|last=Cummins}}</ref>\n\nThe show was produced for a consortium of broadcasters, including [[Ici Radio-Canada T\u00e9l\u00e9]] and [[Knowledge Network]] in Canada, [[M6 (France)|M6]] and [[Piwi +]] in France, [[Zweites Deutsches Fernsehen|ZDF]] in Germany, [[Vlaamse Radio- en Televisieomroeporganisatie|VRT]] in Belgium, and [[Radio T\u00e9l\u00e9vision Suisse|RTS]] in Switerzland.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2016/tv/global/gaumont-zdf-team-on-belle-et-sebastien-1201698234/|title=Gaumont Television, ZDF Team on 'Belle et Sebastien'|first=Else|last=Keslassy|date=February 2, 2016|accessdate=June 2, 2018|work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]|publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]]}}</ref>\n\n==Broadcast==\nThe series first began airing on [[Ici Radio-Canada T\u00e9l\u00e9]] on September 9, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ici.radio-canada.ca/jeunesse/scolaire/blogues/211/5-super-nouvelles-emissions/blogue|title=5 super nouvelles \u00e9missions|date=September 4, 2017|work=[[Ici Radio-Canada T\u00e9l\u00e9]]|publisher=[[Canadian Broadcasting Corporation]]|accessdate=June 2, 2018}}</ref> It premiered in France on [[M6 (France)|M6]] on October 9, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blog.gaumont.fr/2017/09/belle-et-sebastien-debarquent-sur-vos-petits-ecrans/|title=Belle et S\u00e9bastien d\u00e9barquent sur vos petits \u00e9crans !|date=September 20, 2017|accessdate=June 2, 2018|work=Gaumont Le Blog|publisher=[[Gaumont Film Company]]}}</ref> In the United States, the series began airing on [[TiVi5MONDE]] on June 13, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/Tivi5MondeUSA/videos/1820840601309147/|title=\"Belle et S\u00e9bastien\" on TiVi5MONDE starting June 13|work=[[TiVi5MONDE]]|date=June 12, 2018|accessdate=December 18, 2018}}</ref> In Germany, the show premiered on [[KiKa]] on September 22, 2018.<ref>{{cite press-release|url=https://www.presseportal.de/pm/6535/4065638|title=Freundschaft zwischen Kind und Hund: \"Belle und Sebastian\" (ZDF) Premiere der 52-teiligen Animationsserie ab 22. September 2018 bei KiKA|date=September 19, 2018|accessdate=December 18, 2018|publisher=[[ARD (broadcaster)|ARD]]/[[ZDF]]|location=Erfurt|agency=Presse Portal}}</ref>\n\nThe show had its English language debut on [[Knowledge Network]] on October 7, 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.facebook.com/knowledgekids/videos/961989060625640/|title=Knowledge Kids Posts|work=[[Knowledge Network]]|date=September 29, 2017|accessdate=June 2, 2018}}</ref> In Singapore, it began airing on [[Channel 5 (Singapore)|Channel 5's]] [[Okto]] block on June 7, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://tv.toggle.sg/en/channel5/shows/belle-sebastian/info|title=Belle & Sebastian Show Info|work=[[Okto]]|publisher=[[Mediacorp]]|accessdate=June 11, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n[[Category:2010s Canadian animated television series]]\n[[Category:2010s French animated television series]]\n[[Category:2017 French television series debuts]]\n[[Category:2017 Canadian television series debuts]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated adventure television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:Canadian children's animated drama television series]]\n[[Category:French children's animated adventure television series]]\n[[Category:French children's animated comedy television series]]\n[[Category:French children's animated drama television series]]\n[[Category:Gaumont Animation]]\n", "name_user": "Sandstein", "label": "safe", "comment": "Removing link(s):Wikipedia:Articles for deletion/Jessica Kardosclosed as delete (XFDcloser)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Belle_and_Sebastian_(2017_TV_series)"}
